<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17630706-23">
               <interp inst="t17630706-23" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17630706-23" type="year" value="1763"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17630706-23" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17630706"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17630706-23" type="date" value="17630706"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17630706-23-off125-c164" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-23-defend212 t17630706-23-off125 t17630706-23-verdict127"></join>
         
               <p>288. (M.) 
               <persName id="t17630706-23-defend212" type="defendantName">
                  Pearcey 
                  Gouldin 
               <interp inst="t17630706-23-defend212" type="surname" value="Gouldin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-defend212" type="given" value="Pearcey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-defend212" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17630706-23-off125" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-off125" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-off125" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one pair of silver buckles, val. 20 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               <persName id="t17630706-23-victim213" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
                  Hall 
               <interp inst="t17630706-23-victim213" type="surname" value="Hall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-victim213" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-victim213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-23-off125 t17630706-23-victim213"></join>
                  </persName>
             , <rs id="t17630706-23-cd126" type="crimeDate">June 28</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-23-off125 t17630706-23-cd126"></join>. ||</p>
               <p>Thomas Hall. I belong to the Hanover Packet. The prisoner worked three or four days on board, in the steerage where my hammock was, my buckles were in my waistcoat-pocket in my hammock, I missed them on the 28th of June, he was then on board; they were found again at Mr. Jerviso's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17630706-23-person214">
                  Thomas 
                  Jervise 
               <interp inst="t17630706-23-person214" type="surname" value="Jervise"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-person214" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-person214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a goldsmith at Wapping, Old Stairs; a person, very much like the prisoner, brought these buckles to me on the 28th of June, about 6 in the evening, he wanted to sell them, saying they were his own; I weighed them, and gave him 23 s. and 6 d. for them. I do believe the prisoner is the same person. (Produced and deposed to by prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17630706-23-person215">
                  Michael 
                  Bates 
               <interp inst="t17630706-23-person215" type="surname" value="Bates"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-person215" type="given" value="Michael"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-person215" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Jervise. I was by at the time Mr. Jervise bought the buckles; I am certain the prisoner is the man that sold them; when he was taken I saw him, he had the same dress on as he had before, except a pair of long trowsers.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17630706-23-verdict127" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-verdict127" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17630706-23-punish128" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17630706-23-punish128" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17630706-23-defend212 t17630706-23-punish128"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
